  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Classic Room</strong> sleep two people and surrounding views can be enjoyed from the balcony.</p>
<p><strong>Classic Room Sea View</strong> sleep two people and offer lovely views towards Funchal and the sea.</p>
<p><strong>Superior Room Sea View</strong> sleep two people and have great views towards the harbour and sea.</p>
<p><strong>Deluxe Room</strong> sleep two people and are modern in design.</p>
<p><strong>Deluxe Room Sea View</strong> sleep two people and have great views that can be enjoyed from the balcony.</p>
<p><strong>Studio's</strong> sleep up to three people (extra bed is on request). They have a small kitchenette and dining area.</p>
<p><strong>Deluxe Junior Suite</strong> sleep two people and are spacious with a small kitchenette and living area. </p>
<p><strong>Deluxe Junior Suite Sea View</strong> sleep two people, offer a generous space with a small living area and kitchenette as well as sea views.</p>
<p><strong>General information </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Check in: 3pm</li>
<li>Check out: 11am</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Local fees and taxes</strong></p>
<p>A tourist tax of approx. €2.00 per person per night, for a maximum of 7 nights is payable locally for guests age 13 years and over (subject to change).</p>]]></roomsDescription>
